          "date": "2012-04-08 06:40:11.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Fan Yong",
          "email": "yong.fan@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2012-04-08 06:47:46.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-957 scrub: osd-ldiskfs inode iterator",
        "message": "LU-957 scrub: osd-ldiskfs inode iterator\n\nImplement inode table based iterator against osd-ldiskfs.\nThe kernel thread \"osd_scrub\" scans ldiskfs inode table,\nfor each allocated bit, reads corresponding inode, and\nfeeds OI scrub with it.\n\nFor up layer scrub components, they can reuse the cached\nresults from OSD layer iteration through DT iteration APIs\nto perform their system scanning. That means the OSD layer\niterator will pre-fetch objects for up layer scrub components\nthrough the side-effect of its own iteration.\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <yong.fan@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I584c2873cfb11bd488bc60ba175842c71fb03664\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
